            {
              "id": "CVE-2024-7264-curl",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2024-7264 low vulnerability for curl package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in libcurl, where libcurl's ASN1 parser code has the `GTime2str()` function, used for parsing an ASN.1 Generalized Time field. If a syntactically incorrect field is given, the parser can use -1 for the length of the *time fraction*, leading to a `strlen()` performed on a pointer to a heap buffer area that is not purposely NULL terminated."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-7264",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2024-7264\nSeverity: low\nPackage: curl\nVersion: 7.76.1-40.el9\nFix Version: \nType: rpm\nLocation: /var/lib/rpm/rpmdb.sqlite\nData Namespace: redhat:distro:redhat:9\nLink: [CVE-2024-7264](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-7264)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2024-7264**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| low  | curl  | 7.76.1-40.el9  |   | rpm  | /var/lib/rpm/rpmdb.sqlite  | redhat:distro:redhat:9  | [CVE-2024-7264](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-7264)  |\n"
