            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-5450-glibc",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-5450 medium vulnerability for glibc package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in glibc (GNU C Library). This vulnerability occurs when an application uses the `scanf` family of functions with a `%mc` format specifier, which is used for dynamically allocating memory for character input, and provides an explicit width greater than 1024. This specific combination can lead to a one-byte heap buffer overflow, potentially allowing an attacker to corrupt memory."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2026-5450",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-5450\nSeverity: medium\nPackage: glibc\nVersion: 2.34-270.el9_8\nFix Version: \nType: rpm\nLocation: /var/lib/rpm/rpmdb.sqlite\nData Namespace: redhat:distro:redhat:9\nLink: [CVE-2026-5450](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2026-5450)",
